Revision history for RPi-GPIOExpander-MCP23017

1.04 UNREL
    - Documented the A2/A1/A0 hardware address pin to I2C address mapping
      (0x20-0x27) in the new() POD, including a note that the pins must be
      hard-wired and cannot be left floating
<<<<<<< HEAD
    - Added copy of datasheet in docs/
    - Added TECHNICAL INFORMATION POD (DEVICE SPECIFICS, REGISTER MAP, ON THE
      WIRE, DATASHEET): chip capabilities, wiring, the full BANK=0 register
      table cross-referenced to RPi::Const's :mcp23017_registers, the exact
      I2C frames the XS produces, and why register() keeps IOCON locked;
      verified against DS20001952C
    - Bundled datasheet is now referenced locally in the DATASHEET POD via
      docs/MCP23017-Data-Sheet-DS20001952.pdf (was a web URL) and added to
      MANIFEST; corrected the cited revision to the shipped DS20001952D
    - IOCON (0x0A/0x0B) is no longer treated as read-only: register() can now
      set its functional bits (MIRROR, SEQOP, DISSLW, HAEN, ODR, INTPOL); a
      write that would set the BANK bit (bit 7) croaks, since BANK=1 re-maps
      the register layout the module assumes. INTF/INTCAP stay read-only
    - Fixed writePin() to read-modify-write the OLAT register instead of
      GPIO; reading GPIO sampled live pin levels, so a floating input pin
      on the same bank could be latched back as an output value
    - Added an exportable :banks tag (and :all) for the BANK_A/BANK_B bank
      selectors; these are the only constants this module exports. The named
      pin numbers A0-A7/B0-B7 now live in RPi::Const (:mcp23017_pins)
    - Documented in the PIN METHODS POD that A7 (pin 7) and B7 (pin 15) are
      output-only and not reliable as inputs
    - Bump prereq of RPi::Const to 1.06
    - Fixed the GPIO__pinBit() out-of-bounds croak: its "%d" format had no
      argument, printing garbage instead of the offending pin number
    - Fixed t/35-pullup.t and t/40-pullup_bank.t, whose bad-param/no-state
      blocks tested mode_bank() instead of pullup()/pullup_bank(), leaving the
      pullup validation paths effectively untested
    - Added t/02-validation.t: ungated, HW-free coverage of _pinBit() (the
      pin->bank-bit map + out-of-bounds croak) and the _check_bank/_check_mode/
      _check_pullup/_check_write argument validators

1.03    2026-06-12
    - Makefile.PL's i2c presence check can now be bypassed with
      RPI_DIST_RELEASE=1 so release tarballs can be cut on non-Pi
      machines; without it the check still exits before WriteMakefile
      (CPAN testers report NA, not FAIL)

1.02    2019-10-23
    - merged PR from Mohammad S. Anwar that added a missed file in
      MANIFEST
    - moved test run variables to BEGIN block
    - updated pod-coverage testing

1.01    2019-10-19
    - correct typo in variable assignment in POD's SYNOPSIS (closes #2)
    - added extra check in all test files to ensure that an extra env var
      (RPI_SUBMODULE_TESTING) is set, as we literally only want
      RPi::WiringPi's test platform executing the entire test suite (work
      on stevieb9/rpi-wiringpi#159)

1.00    2018-06-15
    - added check in Makefile.PL for linux/i2c.h. CPAN Testers was breaking
      on non-i2c-enabled systems

0.01    2018-06-07
    - initial public release
    - most core registers available
    - ability to change a single pin, a pin bank, or all pins at once
    - read(), write(), mode(), pullup() methods available for single pins,
      a pin bank and all pins
    - exposed register() and register_bits(), but these are more-or-less
      hidden in documentation and we advise they shouldn't really be used;
      they are a convenience for those who know how to understand IC
      registers
    - 5000+ tests

